issue.title: AI Serving ONNX model install and ONNX Runtime library missing

repository.name: ai-serving
repository.description: Serving AI/ML models in the open standard formats PMML and ONNX with both HTTP (REST API) and gRPC endpoints

issue.body:
Hello, I got the AI Serving Server up and running, however when I install the ONNX Resnet50 model, the curl command fails, and can not find the Onnx Runtime extension dependencies.

Do you have any idea where these dependencies are, and how to install them?  I didn't see that in the build instructions. 


curl -X PUT --data-binary @./resnet50v2/resnet50-v2-7.onnx -H "Content-Type: application/octet-stream"  http://localhost:9090/v1/validate

{"error":"Onnx Runtime initialization failed: no onnxruntime in java.library.path: [/Users/h/torch/install/lib, ., /Users/h/Library/Java/Extensions, /Library/Ja((base) MacBoo(base) MacBook-Pro:~/ai-servi(base) MacBook-Pro:~/ai-se(base) MacBook-Pro:~(ba(base(bas(((ba(base) Mac(base) Ma((base(((b(ba((b(base) M(base) Mac(ba(ba((ba(b(ba(bas((base) MacBook-Pro:~/ai-serving-master quantum-fusion$

body: Were you able to solve this error ? We have CI pipelines that run on every PR for Mac and it seems to build fine...
This not resolved, and is open.
['git', 'submodule', 'update', '--init', '--recursive'] doesn't seem to have run properly. Can you please try running git submodule update --init in a fresh clone ?

@snnn I found that the folder /cmake/external/re2 was empty, based on downloading a zip file from the GitHub web gui.  I did verify that was the bug, however when I deleted the repo and started over with a git clone, upon inspection, I find that the /cmake/external/re2 directory is no longer empty, and I have listed its contents.

In addition, I also ran, per the previous post:
(venv) (base) MacBook-Pro:~/onnxruntime quantum-fusion$ git submodule update --init

See transcript below.
